    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We strongly recommend using a tab-separated format while exporting; an example can be found in GitHub: https://github.com/hankemeierlab/mzQuality. Additionally, it is important that numbers and symbols are compatible with R. The input file should include the following columns with the specified headers (Table ): aliquot, type, batch, compound, area, and datetime of the sample measurement.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms tab-separated input format and R compatibility, but does not name or describe a 'buildExperiment' function. The paper describes data input validation and processing steps but does not explicitly mention SummarizedExperiment object construction or a function by that name.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the buildExperiment SummarizedExperiment construction step from a tab-delimited input file",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:26:42.946633+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The first step involves IS normalization, where for all samples ratios are calculated by dividing the compound area (Peak area_compound) by the corresponding IS area (Peak area_IS) as shown in eq . 1 Ratio=Peakarea_compoundPeakarea_IS",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes ratio computation from compound and internal standard areas, but does not mention a 'buildExperiment' function or explicit SummarizedExperiment object construction. The function name and object type are not found in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Does the buildExperiment function correctly construct a SummarizedExperiment object with a computed ratio assay when given a data frame with specified column mappings for compounds, samples, and internal standards?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:26:42.946633+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
