    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality performs several important quality control steps, such as identifying sample outliers, calculating background signal, performing batch correction, detecting trends in total signal intensity for either metabolite or IS, and calculating metrics that highlight variations in metabolite/IS ratios.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes batch correction and outlier detection performed by mzQuality, but does not name a specific function called 'doAnalysis'. The paper describes the overall workflow and output assays but does not reference a function with this name in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the doAnalysis quality-control and batch-correction step to produce the ratio_corrected assay",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:27:02.255901+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The next steps involve the identification of QC and study sample outliers using Rosner's test. For QC samples, outliers are identified based on the median area/area_IS ratios, as these samples are assumed to be identical, while for study samples, only the IS areas are used since they may vary biologically. Potential outliers are flagged by mzQuality and are automatically excluded from further calculations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes outlier identification and batch correction processes, but does not name a function 'doAnalysis' or explicitly describe processing of SummarizedExperiment objects in the provided passages. The functional description matches but the specific function name and data structure are not confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the doAnalysis function process a SummarizedExperiment object to identify outliers and mis-injections, and what corrected assay does it produce?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:27:02.255901+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Batchcorrectedarearatio=fcorrection_batch_n\u00d7arearatio. When trends occur within batches, such as a decrease in sensitivity, mzQuality can correct for this using a within-batch correction. The within-batch correction is performed using a first-order regression.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes batch-corrected area ratios and within-batch correction, but does not explicitly mention output as a 'SummarizedExperiment object' or an assay named 'ratio_corrected'. The paper states 'with an R-compatible output, the data are ready for statistical analysis' but does not specify SummarizedExperiment format in provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "SummarizedExperiment object with 'ratio_corrected' assay containing batch-corrected Compound/Internal Standard ratios",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:27:02.255901+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For QC samples, outliers are identified based on the median area/area_IS ratios, as these samples are assumed to be identical, while for study samples, only the IS areas are used since they may vary biologically. Potential outliers are flagged by mzQuality and are automatically excluded from further calculations.",
      "asbval:note": null,
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
