      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/batch-corrected-data-extraction/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality is distributed as an R package for which version 4.0 or later is required. It is available through GitHub: https://github.com/hankemeierlab/mzQuality... mzQuality performs several important quality control steps, such as identifying sample outliers, calculating background signal, performing batch correction... Batchcorrectedarearatio=fcorrection_batch_n\u00d7arearatio",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms mzQuality performs batch correction and calculates corrected ratios. However, paper does not mention SummarizedExperiment as the storage container for corrected ratios. The paper describes output as 'Excel files that can be used for statistical analysis in tools such as R' and mentions 'R-compatible output', but does not explicitly state that corrected ratios are stored in SummarizedExperiment assay slots.",
