    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The RSDqc is calculated per compound according to eq. 4... Blank samples are used to assess the background signal. The background signal is calculated according to eq. 5... Based on the recommendations of the metabolomics quality assurance and quality control consortium, we set the threshold for the RSDqc at 30%. For the background signal, we recommend that the value of the e-score should not exceed 40%. However, mzQuality allows users to adjust these settings according to their preferences and analytical methods.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms RSDQC, background signal percentage, presence in QC samples, and configurable thresholds. However, 'matrix effect' is not explicitly mentioned as a calculated metric in the paper. The paper focuses on RSDqc (relative standard deviation of QC samples), background signal, and detection percentage, but does not describe a 'matrix effect' metric.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Assess batch effects in metabolomics mass spectrometry data by calculating quality metrics (RSDQC, background signal percentage, matrix effect, presence in QC samples) on pooled study quality control (SQC) samples and applying configurable thresholds to flag unreliable compounds ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:20.376596+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality uses repeat measurements of quality control samples to flag compounds that do not reach predefined thresholds as low quality... Compounds are organized into three tabs based on quality and user-defined or default settings: the 'High confidence' tab includes compounds with RSDqc values below 15%, the 'With Caution' tab includes compounds with RSDqc values ranging between 15% and 30%, and the 'Low Signal to Noise' tab including compounds with either background signal >40% or RSDqc values >30%.",
      "asbval:note": "Directly supported: compounds are flagged and classified into confidence levels for reporting.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill identifies which analytes and injections are affected by systematic variation and aids in selecting reportable results.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:20.376596+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Targeted Mass Spectrometry (MS)-based analytical techniques are often used to detect and quantify hundreds of metabolites simultaneously. Mass spectrometers are generally combined with separation techniques, such as liquid chromatography (LC)... It is important to consider whether to use LQC, SQC, or a combination of both in the batch design, as these samples are used for batch correction and assessment of technical variation.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms LC-MS/MS, batch organization, and SQC use. However, 'matrix effects' are not explicitly discussed as a metric assessed by mzQuality in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have processed metabolomics LC-MS/MS data organized by batch and sample type (including pooled QC replicates), and you need to quantify whether batch-to-batch and matrix effects are acceptable for downstream reporting.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:20.376596+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The first step involves IS normalization, where for all samples ratios are calculated by dividing the compound area (Peak area_compound) by the corresponding IS area (Peak area_IS)... we set the threshold for the RSDqc at 30%. For the background signal, we recommend that the value of the e-score should not exceed 40%.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms IS normalization, RSDQC thresholds (15%, 30%), and background signal threshold (40%). However, the paper does not mention SummarizedExperiment as the data structure used by mzQuality. The paper describes tab-separated input files and R package output, but does not explicitly reference SummarizedExperiment objects.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Specifically, when you have a SummarizedExperiment object with internal-standard-normalized peak areas and you need to decide which compounds meet quality thresholds (e.g., RSDQC \u2264 15\u201330%, background signal \u2264 40%) and which samples are statistical outliers.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:20.376596+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality is distributed as an R package for which version 4.0 or later is required. It is available through GitHub: https://github.com/hankemeierlab/mzQuality... mzQuality performs several important quality control steps, such as identifying sample outliers, calculating background signal, performing batch correction, detecting trends in total signal intensity for either metabolite or IS, and calculating metrics that highlight variations in metabolite/IS ratios.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms mzQuality is an R package that computes RSDQC, background signal, and presence metrics. However, the paper does not mention a function called 'doAnalysis()' explicitly, nor does it describe 'matrix effect' as a computed metric. The paper describes the overall workflow but does not name the specific function.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "batch-effect-assessment-via-quality-metrics",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "mzQuality: Core R package that implements doAnalysis() to compute all batch and quality metrics (RSDQC, background, matrix effect, presence) and assign use flags based on thresholds",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:20.376596+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
