    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compound-reliability-filtering-by-rsd-threshold/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Once all of the batch corrections are performed, various metrics are calculated to check the quality of compounds. The RSDqc is calculated using the QC samples both before and after batch correction to evaluate the stability of a compound during measurements. ... If SQCs were generated from pooling study samples, then they provide an average signal over the study samples, therefore allowing a direct comparison with the samples investigated with the biological samples.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms RSD filtering is applied post-batch-correction using SQC samples.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compound-reliability-filtering-by-rsd-threshold",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this filter after batch correction of compound/internal-standard ratios when you have pooled study quality control (SQC) samples",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:53.696225+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compound-reliability-filtering-by-rsd-threshold/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Based on the recommendations of the metabolomics quality assurance and quality control consortium, we set the threshold for the RSDqc at 30%. ... Compounds are organized into three tabs based on quality and user-defined or default settings: the 'High confidence' tab includes compounds with RSDqc values below 15%, the 'With Caution' tab includes compounds with RSDqc values ranging between 15% and 30%, and the 'Low Signal to Noise' tab including compounds with either background signal >40% or RSDqc values >30%.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms the 30% RSD threshold and compound classification by quality. However, the specific function name 'doAnalysis' and object field 'rowData$use' are not mentioned in the paper\u2014these are Bioconductor implementation details not detailed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compound-reliability-filtering-by-rsd-threshold",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when the nonReportableRSD threshold (e.g., 30%) has been set in doAnalysis and you are deciding which compounds in rowData$use should be marked TRUE or FALSE",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:30:53.696225+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/compound-standard-ratio-normalization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The first step involves IS normalization, where for all samples ratios are calculated by dividing the compound area (Peak area_compound) by the corresponding IS area (Peak area_IS)... To correct for technical variation between individual batches by, e.g., sample preparation, mobile phases, column changes, instrument cleaning, or changes in sensitivity of the system over time, a between-batch correction is performed.",
      "asbval:note": "Claim is directly supported. The paper describes IS normalization as the first step and explicitly links it to correcting for technical variation from sample preparation and instrument sensitivity changes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "compound-standard-ratio-normalization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Normalize metabolomics compound abundances by calculating ratios between each compound and its assigned internal standard to account for instrument response variation and sample preparation differences. This foundational preprocessing step enables downstream batch correction and ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:31:12.123830+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
