    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/internal-standard-area-mis-injection-flagging/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For study samples, only the IS areas are used since they may vary biologically. Potential outliers are flagged by mzQuality and are automatically excluded from further calculations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes outlier detection on IS areas using Rosner's test, but does not explicitly frame this as 'mis-injection' detection or test whether IS areas fall outside 'expected ranges'. The paper states outliers are identified based on IS areas for study samples, but the functional purpose is broader outlier detection, not specifically mis-injection flagging. The paper does mention 'Rosner's test is used on the IS of study samples to identify and flag potential misinjections and, thus, outliers' in passage [3], which supports the mis-injection framing.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "internal-standard-area-mis-injection-flagging",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Detect and flag mis-injected study samples in metabolomics LC-MS data by testing whether Internal Standard peak areas fall outside expected ranges, identifying technical failures that compromise quantitation reliability.",
