    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-ratio-batch-correction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To correct for technical variation between individual batches by, e.g., sample preparation, mobile phases, column changes, instrument cleaning, or changes in sensitivity of the system over time, a between-batch correction is performed... batch-to-batch compound-specific correction factors are calculated using eq and multiplied by the area ratios of each compound... If SQCs were generated from pooling study samples, then they provide an average signal over the study samples, therefore allowing a direct comparison with the samples investigated with the biological samples.",
      "asbval:note": "Core research question is directly supported by the paper's description of batch correction methodology using QC samples.",
