    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-ratio-batch-correction/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The input file should include the following columns with the specified headers (Table ): aliquot, type, batch, compound, area, and datetime of the sample measurement. For quantitative or semiquantitative analysis, the columns compound_is and area_is must also be included... The example data set comprises 6 random yet consecutively measured batches containing 419 EDTA plasma study samples... Also included in the batches were different types of QC samples, blank samples, and calibration curves.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes input data structure with multiple batches, study samples, QC replicates, and calibration lines with ion areas and internal standards. However, input format is tab-separated text file, not SummarizedExperiment objects.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-ratio-batch-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input is a SummarizedExperiment containing multiple batches or injection sequences of metabolomics samples (study samples, QC replicates, calibration lines) with measured ion areas for compounds and assigned internal standards.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:06.844624+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-ratio-batch-correction/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality provides an accessible solution to improve the data quality without requiring prior programming skills. Its customizable settings integrate seamlessly into research workflows, enhancing the accuracy and reproducibility of the metabolomics data. Additionally, with an R-compatible output, the data are ready for statistical analysis and biological interpretation.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that mzQuality harmonizes data across batches using QC samples and produces output ready for statistical analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-ratio-batch-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you need to harmonize compound/internal standard ratios across batches before downstream quantitation or statistical modeling, especially when pooled QC samples are available to estimate batch-specific correction factors.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:06.844624+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-ratio-batch-correction/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "If SQCs were generated from pooling study samples, then they provide an average signal over the study samples, therefore allowing a direct comparison with the samples investigated with the biological samples... When a compound is not detected in LQC or SQC samples, the compound will be assumed to not be present and will not be reported by mzQuality.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that QC samples are essential for batch correction and compound assessment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-ratio-batch-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input data lacks pooled quality control samples \u2014 batch correction requires QC replicates to estimate batch-specific factors.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:06.844624+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-ratio-batch-correction/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Whenever more than one batch is present, a batch correction is performed to minimize batch-to-batch variation in the data... If no batches are defined, all samples are assigned to batch 1.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms batch correction is only performed when multiple batches are present.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolite-ratio-batch-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: All samples are from a single batch or injection sequence \u2014 batch correction is not applicable; calculate uncorrected ratios instead.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:06.844624+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-data-input-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality performs a validation on the input file to ensure all necessary information is included and to detect any formatting errors. It checks for the presence of the required columns and verifies whether a batch is assigned to all aliquots... During the validation process, mzQuality checks if the column \"type\" includes the sample type QC. Additionally, it verifies if there is an observation for every aliquot and every compound and inserts \"NA\" for any missing data.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms tab-delimited validation and column checking, but does NOT mention SummarizedExperiment object construction. mzQuality outputs Excel files and R-compatible data for downstream analysis, not explicit SummarizedExperiment construction. The card conflates mzQuality's output format with Bioconductor's SummarizedExperiment class, which is not mentioned in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-data-input-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validate tab-delimited metabolomics data files for mandatory column presence, correct format, and data integrity before constructing a SummarizedExperiment object.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:26.790795+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-data-input-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality performs a validation on the input file to ensure all necessary information is included and to detect any formatting errors... If any of the necessary columns are absent, mzQuality will not be able to run.",
      "asbval:note": "Validation prevents malformed input from propagating; confirmed as upstream quality gate.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
