      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-quality-metric-interpretation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The RSDqc is calculated per compound according to eq. 4... Blank samples are used to assess the background signal... Based on the recommendations of the metabolomics quality assurance and quality control consortium, we set the threshold for the RSDqc at 30%. For the background signal, we recommend that the value of the e-score should not exceed 40%.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses RSDQC, background signal percentage, and presence in QC samples. However, 'matrix effect' is not mentioned in the passages. The paper does discuss IS selection and quality assessment, but does not explicitly frame this as selecting 'optimal internal standards based on quantitative thresholds' in the way the card describes.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-quality-metric-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Interpret and apply quality control metrics (RSDQC, background signal percentage, matrix effect, presence in QC samples) to identify reliable compounds and internal standards in batch-corrected metabolomics data.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:58.952325+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-quality-metric-interpretation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To correct for technical variation between individual batches... a between-batch correction is performed... The RSDqc is calculated using the QC samples both before and after batch correction to evaluate the stability of a compound during measurements... ISs can be predefined in the input file and should be selected based on class behavior and retention times. mzQuality also provides suggestions for alternative ISs... These suggestions are based on calculations that evaluate all compound and IS combinations to determine which combination gives the best RSDqc after batch correction.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported: paper describes batch correction using QC samples, RSDQC calculation, and IS selection based on minimizing RSDQC.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-quality-metric-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After batch correction of metabolomics data using pooled study quality control (SQC) samples and calculation of compound/internal standard ratios, when you need to decide which compounds are reliable for reporting and which internal standard minimizes technical variation (RSDQC) ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:32:58.952325+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-quality-metric-interpretation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mzQuality is distributed as an R package for which version 4.0 or later is required. It is available through GitHub: https://github.com/hankemeierlab/mzQuality... mzQuality uses repeat measurements of quality control samples to flag compounds that do not reach predefined thresholds as low quality. We defined the threshold at a relative standard deviation of QC > 30%... mzQuality also provides suggestions for alternative ISs... These suggestions are based on calculations that evaluate all compound and IS combinations to determine which combination gives the best RSDqc after batch correction.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported: mzQuality is confirmed as an R package that calculates RSDQC and flags compounds based on thresholds, and evaluates IS combinations.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-jasms-5c00073",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-quality-metric-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "mzQuality - Primary R package that exhaustively calculates RSDQC values across all internal standard candidates and flags compounds as reliable or unreliable based on quality thresholds",
